Three police officers, Sello Tsima (36), and Edward Magape (46), from Wierdabrug police station and Massifo Johannes Mangena (37), from Midrand police station, were granted bail while Congolese national Alain Mbembe (48), was denied bail by the Pretoria Magistrates` Court. Tsima and Magape, are facing charges of kidnapping, corruption and defeating the ends of justice, while Mangena and Mbembe, are facing charges of kidnapping and corruption. ALSO READ: add bookmark Man shot, injured in business robbery! The National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) spokeswoman Lumka Mahanjana said it is alleged that on 17 May 2021, one of the complainants and Mbembe went to Wierdabrug police station in Centurion to open a case of housebreaking and theft against three young ladies, who were attending a house party hosted by the complainant. She said while at the police station, Tsima who is an investigating officer and Magape told the complainant that he should pay them an amount of R10000 to investigate the case. “The following day, Mbembe and Mangena forcefully took the three ladies to the Wierdabrug police station where they were detained overnight.” You must be SIGNED IN to read comments “On 19 May 2021, Tsima and Magape requested the family members to pay an amount of R10 000 to release the three ladies. After accepting the money, Tsima informed the complainant who opened the case against the three ladies that they will appear in court the following day,” said Mahanjana. She added that when the complainant arrived in court, he was informed that there was no court appearance, he then proceeded to Wierdabrug police station to report the matter. “All accused were arrested on 14 February 2023, after an identity parade was conducted. The case has been remanded for 27 February 2023 for the state to acquire a report about Mbembe’s legal status from Home Affairs,” said Mahajana.